2064.subject: SW
2064.descrlong: Builds upon the knowledge, skills, and attitudes acquired in SW 310 and contains three distinct modules: (1) provides students with a conceptual approach to assessing clients and their situations, and planning effective interventions; (2) advances students¿ interviewing skills; and (3) enhances students¿ cross cultural competency. (Offered spring semester.)
